---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Mission Sikhism"
  description="Mission Sikhism is a non-profit, community-built, fully-sourced history of the Sikh faith."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
        Mission Sikhism is a non-profit, community-built history of the Sikh
        faith, from 1469 to today. Its guiding promise is simple: every fact is
        sourced. That promise is enforced by the build itself — a page cannot go
        live if any claim on it lacks a citation.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contribute">Contribute</h2>
      <p>
        The site is built from plain Markdown files in a public repository. To
        contribute, submit a change with a citation for every factual claim, and
        a maintainer will review it before it goes live. A full contributor
        guide is coming soon.
      </p>

      <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
      <h3>Why is everything sourced?</h3>
      <p>
        Sikh history is often retold without references. This site takes the
        opposite approach: if a fact can't be cited, it doesn't ship.
      </p>
      <h3>How are the eras divided?</h3>
      <p>
        History is organised into eras from 1469 to today. The framing is meant
        to be clear and faithful to the tradition — feedback is welcome.
      </p>
      <h3>Can I reuse this content?</h3>
      <p>
        Mission Sikhism is a community resource. Licensing details will be
        published here.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
